 <text>
  <front>
   <head>VERSE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">YOU ask why in that garland fair,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Where various sweets abound,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A  flow'r of merit rare</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Is no where to be found?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why the same florist thought not meet</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To give that bloom its due?</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Since none can odours yield more sweet,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Or boast a brighter hue.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then know, the modest swain, my friend,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Who cull'd those flow'rs so gay,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Meant others worth to recommend,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And not his own display.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But if this blooming wreath had been</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Twin'd by another's care,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Dodsley, thy flow'r, we then had seen</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Shining distinguish'd there.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
